article.headline: Kansas 79, Albany, N.Y. 43
article.story: LAWRENCE, Kan. -- Cole Aldrich had 20 points, Tyrel Reed added 12 and Kansas shot 56 percent in a 79-43 rout of Albany, N.Y., on Tuesday night. Kansas (9-3) was coming off a difficult loss, an 84-67 setback at Arizona in its first true road game of the season. The Jayhawks took a week off and didn't have any trouble with Albany (8-5), dominating both ends for their 31st straight win at Allen Fieldhouse. Kansas took control with an early 11-0 run and built the lead to 21 points in the first half, maintaining it by hitting 9-of-19 from 3-point range overall. Albany had all kinds of trouble with Kansas' pressure defense, forced to take deep 3-pointers or offbalance shots late in the shot clock. The Great Danes shot 8-of-33 in the first half to trail 40-19 at halftime and shot 30 percent overall, missing all 15 of their 3-point attempts. Anthony Raffa led Albany with 11 points.
